CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Correctional Services – Private Immigration Detention Facilities – Zoning
3 Requirement
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the State or a unit of local government from approving the
5 use of a building or, a structure, or other real property for use as an immigration a
6 detention facility by a private entity unless certain zoning authority applies;
7 establishing a certain penalty for a certain violation; authorizing the Attorney
8 General to bring a civil action to enforce this Act; applying this Act retroactively; and
9 generally relating to immigration detention facilities.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – Correctional Services
12 Section 1–101(a) and (j)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume)
15 BY adding to
16 Article – Correctional Services
17 Section 1–103
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume)
20 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
21 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0984*

2 SENATE BILL 984
1 Article – Correctional Services
2 1–101.
3 (a) In this article the following words have the meanings indicated.
4 (j) “Immigration detention facility” means any building, facility, or structure
5 used, in whole or in part, to house or detain individuals for federal civil immigration
6 violations.
7 1–103.
8 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
9 INDICATED.
10 (2) (I) “DETENTION FACILITY” MEANS ANY BUILDING, FACILITY,
11 OR STRUCTURE USED, IN WHOLE OR IN PART, TO HOUSE OR DETAIN INDIVIDUALS
12 FOR CIVIL OR CRIMINAL VIOLATIONS.
13 (II) “DETENTION FACILITY” INCLUDES AN IMMIGRATION
14 DETENTION FACILITY.
15 (3) “UNIT OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT” MEANS A COUNTY, A
16 MUNICIPALITY, OR THE MARYLAND NATIONAL CAPITAL PARK AND PLANNING
17 COMMISSION.
18 (A) (B) (1) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, THE
19 STATE OR A UNIT OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT MAY NOT APPROVE THE USE
20 CONSTRUCTION OR OPERATION OF A BUILDING OR, A STRUCTURE, OR OTHER REAL
21 PROPERTY AS AN IMMIGRATION FOR A DETENTION FACILITY BY A PRIVATE ENTITY
22 UNLESS IMMIGRATION DETENTION FACILITY IS EXPRESSLY INCLUDED IN THE
23 APPLICABLE ZONING AUTHORITY.
24 (2) A GENERAL ZONING CLASSIFICATION AUTHORIZING
25 GOVERNMENT, PUBLIC, OR INSTITUTIONAL USES DOES NOT CONSTITUTE EXPRESS
26 AUTHORIZATION FOR A BUILDING OR STRUCTURE TO BE USED AS AN IMMIGRATION
27 DETENTION FACILITY BY A PRIVATE ENTITY.
28 (B) (C) A PRIVATE ENTITY MAY NOT OPERATE OR OCCUPY A BUILDING
29 OR, A STRUCTURE, OR OTHER REAL PROPERTY AS AN IMMIGRATION A DETENTION
30 FACILITY WITHOUT A USE AND OCCUPANCY AUTHORIZATION OR CHANGE IN USE AND
31 OCCUPANCY APPROVAL CONSISTENT WITH THIS SECTION.

SENATE BILL 984 3
1 (C) (D) FOR PURPOSES OF THIS SECTION, A BUILDING OR, A STRUCTURE,
2 OR OTHER REAL PROPERTY SHALL BE CONSIDERED PROPOSED FOR USE AS AN
3 IMMIGRATION A DETENTION FACILITY, REGARDLESS OF HOW THE USE IS DESCRIBED
4 IN AN APPLICATION OR PERMIT REQUEST, IF:
5 (1) INDIVIDUALS ARE INTENDED TO BE HELD IN INVOLUNTARY
6 CUSTODY AND WILL NOT BE FREE TO LEAVE; OR
7 (2) THE DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION, OR IMPROVEMENTS INCLUDE
8 FEATURES CONSISTENT WITH SECURE OR INVOLUNTARY CONFINEMENT,
9 INCLUDING:
10 (I) PERIMETER SECURITY MEASURES DESIGNED TO PREVENT
11 OCCUPANTS FROM LEAVING;
12 (II) CONTROLLED ACCESS POINTS; OR
13 (III) LOCKED HOLDING AREAS.
14 (D) (E) (1) THE ATTORNEY GENERAL MAY BRING A CIVIL ACTION TO
15 ENFORCE THIS SECTION.
16 (2) THE COURT MAY ISSUE TEMPORARY, PRELIMINARY, OR
17 PERMANENT INJUNCTIVE RELIEF TO PREVENT AN ACT THAT WOULD CONSTITUTE A
18 VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION.
19 (E) (F) A PRIVATE ENTITY THAT OPERATES OR ATTEMPTS TO OPERATE
20 AN IMMIGRATION A DETENTION FACILITY IN VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION IS
21 SUBJECT TO A CIVIL PENALTY NOT EXCEEDING $10,000 FOR EACH DAY THE
22 VIOLATION CONTINUES.
23 (F) (G) THE REMEDIES PROVIDED UNDER THIS SECTION ARE IN
24 ADDITION TO ANY OTHER REMEDY AVAILABLE UNDER STATE OR LOCAL LAW.
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be applied
26 retroactively to any agreement between the State or a unit of local government and a
27 private entity entered into before the effective date of this Act for the use of any building
28 or structure, structure, or other real property if that building or structure, structure, or
29 other real property is intended to be used as an immigration a detention facility, regardless
30 of any permits issued or investment made by the private entity toward construction or
31 renovation of the building or, structure, or other real property.
32 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
33 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has

4 SENATE BILL 984
1 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
2 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
3 enacted.
